Question: Should restaurant be required to display nutritional information in their menu?
Answer:
from my personal aspect. i think restaurants do not need to display nutritional information in their menu. 
there are several reason to support my opinion. first of all, i think most of the food in a restaurant is quite familiar to most people. so i do not think it is necessary. 
second, i think it is not convenient to do that. it will be a lot of word on the menu. it is not easy for customer to find the right one. especially when people do not know the food. 
so i think they are not required to do that. 